node.text:
❤️Congratulations my angel on this incredible new journey with Kin….

This is super special and meaningful…

It’s hard for the world to understand how much you have suffered with mental health and the dis-ease of not having a healthy brain like most people do……. 

Writing this makes me emotional because watching you push through the brain fog everyday for the past 10 years and trying to guide you as your mom & biggest supporter has been one of the hardest things for me to do.  I’m so incredibly proud of your perseverance to find healing, remedies and the proper tools to be the best version of yourself while sharing your story to help others.

“Kin” is a brain care beverage and it’s natural ingredients is a little piece of the wellness pie. perfect for a life style staple as we all search for health and happiness everyday.

Your star shines bright my love and with your heart set on always helping others this is destined for success….. I can’t wait to see all the goodness you will create with @kineuphorics and the entire team that share the same intention #ProudMomma #BrainWellness

node.text:
❤️Nobody will ever look at me the way she did, she knew that I knew and I knew what she knew…
Her eyes spoke a million words…. It has been 2 years this week that I’ve been trying to do life without her but this is a bond that is irreplaceable and I struggle with the emptiness everyday. No matter what happened in my life she was my anchor, the voice of reason and grounding force that kept me humble…… I love you mamma in heaven❤️ #MissingYou

node.text:
❤️I put a lot of emphasis on teaching my children to love and respect nature, seeing them still climb trees and embrace Mother Nature to ground and connect to their spirituality makes me so happy. 
As a single mom it took a lot to always create outside activities, sports and keeping everybody’s little feet playing in the sand but it was worth every minute as they now have the awareness of its power in their lives…...
It’s much easier to run to the pharmacy then trying to see what mother earth has to offer in herbal and homeopathic remedies.
I think there is much more to learn in nature then in front of a tv, phone or computer…. I think it develops very different skills and much more resilient human beings……. #Motherhood
#FarmLife
